The paper deals with the Hamiltonian cycle problem, which is a classic problem in computer science and falls under the category of computational complexity. The paper specifically focuses on rooted directed path graphs, which are a type of directed acyclic graph. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), followed by cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), and cs.GT (Graph Theory).
